 class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 31, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104taj1665702588022.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/taj1665702588022.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/taj1665702588022.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"taj1665702588022\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      AttributesOnly\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The AttributesOnly DSP widget represents an abstract field to which any HTML element can be bound, making it possible to manipulate its attributes in ProcScript and JavaScript.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"taj1665702588022__section_w1093ab1b5b1_w1094ab1b5_w1095ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"akm1704707836734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/akm1704707836734.html\" title=\"By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves.\">Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"taj1665702588022__table_d13652e1_d13653e1_d13654e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Summary</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Logical Widget Name: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">AttributesOnly </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Maps to Physical Widget : </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">genericHTML</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default definition: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">AttributesOnly=genericHTML</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Supported triggers and properties: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eih1718602085507.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eih1718602085507.html\" title=\"The genericHTML DSP widget can be used to define properties for any HTML element that can be bound to a field, making it possible to manipulate its attributes in ProcScript and JavaScript.\">genericHTML</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Use for: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Manipulating the attributes of HTML element in\n                        ProcScript and JavaScript. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"taj1665702588022__section_w1096ab1b5b3_w1097ab1b5_w1098ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d138540e145\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"taj1665702588022__p_d113906e1_d113907e1_d113908e1\">You can use the AttributesOnly widget to implement tabs for web page navigation, or to change the position and appearance of an individual widget, or to control the appearance of the whole web page or web page section.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjk1665702557273.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Widgets</a><p>In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sno1665702583691.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>Widget definitions for Dynamic Server Pages (DSPs) are used to generate the HTML elements and controls used to represent fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gxl1704704845079.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Logical Widgets</a><p>Logical widgets are named configurations of physical widgets. A single physical widget may therefore have multiple logical widgets mapped to it. For fields, logical widgets provide the only way that physical widgets can be addressed.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oao1665702862509.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Example: Dynamically Change HTML Attributes in ProcScript</a><p>You can use the AttributesOnly widget in dynamic server pages to manipulate HTML in ProcScript.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqr1719489288111.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Entity and Occurrence Properties in Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>In Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the widget properties of entities and occurrences in the runtime component using ProcScript or JavaScript. It is not possible to set these properties declaratively.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532251\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532251\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "AttributesOnly Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 31, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 AttributesOnly The AttributesOnly DSP widget represents an abstract field to which any HTML element can be bound, making it possible to manipulate its attributes in ProcScript and JavaScript. For more information, see Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity . Table 1. Widget Summary Logical Widget Name: AttributesOnly Maps to Physical Widget : genericHTML Default definition: AttributesOnly=genericHTML Supported triggers and properties: See genericHTML Use for: Manipulating the attributes of HTML element in ProcScript and JavaScript. Description You can use the AttributesOnly widget to implement tabs for web page navigation, or to change the position and appearance of an individual widget, or to control the appearance of the whole web page or web page section. Related Links Widgets In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets. Widgets for Dynamic Server Pages Widget definitions for Dynamic Server Pages (DSPs) are used to generate the HTML elements and controls used to represent fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser. Logical Widgets Logical widgets are named configurations of physical widgets. A single physical widget may therefore have multiple logical widgets mapped to it. For fields, logical widgets provide the only way that physical widgets can be addressed. Example: Dynamically Change HTML Attributes in ProcScript You can use the AttributesOnly widget in dynamic server pages to manipulate HTML in ProcScript. Entity and Occurrence Properties in Dynamic Server Pages In Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the widget properties of entities and occurrences in the runtime component using ProcScript or JavaScript. It is not possible to set these properties declaratively. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}